## R Markdown

This is an R Markdown document. Markdown is a simple formatting syntax for authoring HTML, PDF, and MS Word documents. For more details on using R Markdown see <http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com>.

When you click the **Knit** button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

```{r message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, echo=FALSE}
# Core data wrangling
required <- c("tidyverse", "HistData")
new_pkgs <- required[!(required %in% installed.packages()[,"Package"])]
if(length(new_pkgs)) install.packages(new_pkgs)
lapply(required, library, character.only = TRUE)

# Friendly's GDAdata (may come from his R-universe)
if(!"GDAdata" %in% installed.packages()[,"Package"]) {
  install.packages("GDAdata", repos = "https://friendly.r-universe.dev")
}
#install.packages("GDAdata")
library(GDAdata)

# `Nightingale` accompanies Friendly & Meyer, *HistData* pkg
data("Nightingale", package = "HistData")

glimpse(Nightingale)     # sanity check

write_csv(Nightingale,
          file = "case1_nightingale/data/nightingale_raw.csv")


data("Minard.troops", package = "HistData")
data("Minard.temp",   package = "HistData")

glimpse(Minard.troops)
glimpse(Minard.temp)

write_csv(Minard.troops,
          file = "case3_minard/data/minard_troops_raw.csv")
write_csv(Minard.temp,
          file = "case3_minard/data/minard_temp_raw.csv")

data("EastIndiesTrade", package = "GDAdata")   # yearly exports & imports

glimpse(EastIndiesTrade)

write_csv(EastIndiesTrade,
          file = "case2_playfair/data/playfair_raw.csv")


```

## Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

```{r pressure, echo=FALSE}
plot(pressure)
```

Note that the `echo = FALSE` parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
